As part of its commitment to providing fans with the full AFCON experience, MTN Nigeria, the official communications partner of the Nigeria Football Federation (NFF), has struck partnerships with 140 viewing centres across the country. Fans will have opportunity to watch the AFCON matches and take home exciting prizes such as phones, irons, t-shirts, and many more for the duration of the tournament. Some of these centres include Lawancy Bar, Sokoto; Disney Park, Kaduna; Laila Cinema, Yola North/Adamawa; I â€“ Xplore Bar, Jos; Elegantee Garden Bar, Kano; Eden Park & Garden, Abuja; Trybeze Lounge, Akure; Forest Guest Inn, Ilorin; Matrix Lounge, Ibadan; Royalboard Bar & Grill, Oshogbo; Hotel De Treasure, Ile-Ife; Halmod Iwe Royin, Abeokuta; Side Walk Event Center, VI, Lagos; Rehab Bar and Lounge, Benin; Villa Toscana Sports Bar, Enugu; Sugarland, Aba; Sweet Garden, Onitsha; Beer Garden & Sports Bar, Warri and Bulevard Funplace & Bar, Calabar, among others. MTN Nigeria became the official communications partner of the Super Eagles and other national teams after signing a three-year multi-million naira partnership deal with the Nigerian Football Federation (NFF) on September 2, 2021. 